What would her name be?

00:07:13.507 --> 00:07:18.092
I don't know if Lui-senpai
would be okay with that.

00:07:29.093 --> 00:07:31.033
But would you like to hear more songs?

00:07:31.073 --> 00:07:32.474
More cover songs from us?

00:07:33.296 --> 00:07:34.457
What would you like to hear?

00:07:34.924 --> 00:07:37.995
There's a lot of really good
songs so it's hard to decide.

00:07:38.075 --> 00:07:42.147
Actually, it did take us quite a while
to decide which song we wanted

00:07:42.172 --> 00:07:43.977
- to pick for our very first cover.
- It's difficult, y'know?

00:07:43.997 --> 00:07:45.097
There's so many good songs.

00:07:45.177 --> 00:07:46.317
Right, you know?

00:07:46.837 --> 00:07:50.298
And they can show all different
types of you, so, you know?

00:07:50.478 --> 00:07:52.439
There's those kind
of ways to enjoy it too.

00:07:54.046 --> 00:07:56.534
300! 300 of them. Ohh!

00:07:56.559 --> 00:07:59.137
Idol by YOASOBI-san.

00:07:59.971 --> 00:08:02.575
Are we gonna be stuck
just to YOASOBI songs?

00:08:03.496 --> 00:08:04.644
That's not too bad though...

00:08:05.347 --> 00:08:06.504
Ah, Tuning Love?

00:08:07.266 --> 00:08:09.325
Tuning Love's cute too.

00:08:10.288 --> 00:08:11.529
Lots of good suggestions.

00:08:12.050 --> 00:08:15.134
Kagamine Twins.

00:08:15.154 --> 00:08:18.960
We definitely didn't
have that thought too.

00:08:19.601 --> 00:08:21.483
But thank you so much for listening to it.

00:08:21.503 --> 00:08:24.467
We hope that you continue to
enjoy it more and more and more.

00:08:25.669 --> 00:08:27.410
We can hit 1 million?

00:08:28.571 --> 00:08:30.492
That would be a big team.

00:08:30.652 --> 00:08:32.373
Big, big, big team.

00:08:33.103 --> 00:08:35.388
- Let's not get ahead of ourselves.
- No, no, not yet. No.

00:08:36.616 --> 00:08:37.737
Maybe we can in the future.

00:08:39.217 --> 00:08:40.217
Thank you!

00:08:40.678 --> 00:08:46.122
But next, there's been
another misunderstanding.

00:08:50.180 --> 00:08:52.421
Misunderstanding.

00:08:55.483 --> 00:09:02.207
I wanted to say, so last FUWAMOCO
Morning, everyone was discussing tomorrow.

00:09:02.227 --> 00:09:03.588
And you know it.

00:09:03.608 --> 00:09:05.469
I got confused.

00:09:05.930 --> 00:09:09.612
Yeah, because there's a lot
of things I don't understand.

00:09:10.192 --> 00:09:12.714
But I feel like tomorrow isn't one of them.

00:09:13.434 --> 00:09:17.776
I just thought that, you know,
there's two popular movies right now.

00:09:18.337 --> 00:09:20.815
So then I thought maybe
it was something from that

00:09:20.840 --> 00:09:22.834
because there's like a
lot of things I don't know.

00:09:22.859 --> 00:09:26.842
And the senpai members have been
sending us a lot of things I don't know.

00:09:27.342 --> 00:09:32.845
So I thought, but maybe it's from the
movies or maybe it was from Die Hard.

00:09:32.925 --> 00:09:35.286
Since I've never seen that
movie and people like it.

00:09:35.306 --> 00:09:37.600
It seems sort of like something
that would be in Die Hard.

00:09:38.789 --> 00:09:42.029
But no, Moco-chan, you're just like

00:09:42.054 --> 00:09:46.435
"I don't know," lots of things,
so it's probably not that, right?

00:09:46.682 --> 00:09:47.774
- Right.
- Yeah.

00:09:47.799 --> 00:09:51.068
Obviously, we really like hololive, but

00:09:51.093 --> 00:09:53.640
It's very hard to know
everything about hololive.

00:09:54.241 --> 00:09:56.843
But yeah, this was one of them.

00:09:56.963 --> 00:10:02.908
Actually, actually, we took the
official hololive quiz, the <i>hololive Kentei</i>.

00:10:05.097 --> 00:10:06.177
I'm not sure if you did it.

00:10:06.651 --> 00:10:08.776
Unfortunately, you can't take it anymore.

00:10:08.796 --> 00:10:10.399
The testing period is over.

00:10:10.619 --> 00:10:13.285
But we wanted to share our
scores with you, you know?

00:10:17.488 --> 00:10:20.651
<i>hololive ID Kentei</i>,
<i>hololive English Kentei</i>,

00:10:20.675 --> 00:10:24.576
And then <i>hololive JP Kentei</i>.
Even the JP one in Japanese too.

00:10:25.396 --> 00:10:26.678
We passed!

00:10:27.810 --> 00:10:29.160
The official test.

00:10:29.340 --> 00:10:30.722
Official test, you know.

00:10:31.302 --> 00:10:35.747
We were really nervous about
it because they're really hard.

00:10:35.772 --> 00:10:36.772
Really, really hard.

00:10:38.269 --> 00:10:40.392
You know, we study up a lot.

00:10:40.912 --> 00:10:44.777
Maybe we studied a bit too much.

00:10:45.278 --> 00:10:48.581
But we figured, you know, this
would be the least we could do.

00:10:48.642 --> 00:10:52.526
And obviously, by no means does
it mean that we know everything.

00:10:52.546 --> 00:10:53.587
We don't know everything.

00:10:53.607 --> 00:10:55.249
We don't know nothing.

00:11:00.097 --> 00:11:02.280
We'd like to know more
too, but we're also

00:11:02.305 --> 00:11:05.978
We're also very forgetful puppies
when we're under pressure.

00:11:06.378 --> 00:11:11.199
So like, if you were to ask me,
Fuwawa, what are you streaming next?

00:11:11.359 --> 00:11:12.840
I'd be like, I don't know!

00:11:13.540 --> 00:11:14.880
Right, right.

00:11:15.100 --> 00:11:16.721
So we have to make notes sometimes.

00:11:18.481 --> 00:11:21.322
Alright, so more puppies, thank you!

00:11:21.702 --> 00:11:23.862
We're pleased,
Moco-chan, we're pleased.

00:11:25.883 --> 00:11:27.403
It was very fun though, but...

00:11:28.658 --> 00:11:32.760
It reminded me of being back
at Guard Dog Training, right?

00:11:32.780 --> 00:11:34.140
Right.

00:11:34.165 --> 00:11:35.541
- It was tricky.
- It was tricky.

00:11:35.574 --> 00:11:36.574
Tricky, tricky.

00:11:36.661 --> 00:11:40.423
Definitely recommend if they do
<i>hololive Kentei</i> the official quiz again.

00:11:40.588 --> 00:11:42.477
- Right?
- You get your certification.

00:11:42.509 --> 00:11:44.301
- Certification.
- Yeah.

00:11:45.745 --> 00:11:50.647
But also, there's been
another misunderstanding.

00:11:50.867 --> 00:11:52.748
This time it wasn't Mococo.

00:11:55.109 --> 00:11:56.310
It was me.

00:11:56.890 --> 00:12:02.639
During our Question and Answer
stream, I picked up a comment about

00:12:02.664 --> 00:12:08.716
Takenoko vs Kinoko, which is Takenoko's
bamboo shoots and Kinoko's mushrooms.

00:12:09.807 --> 00:12:16.941
I thought, you know, the yummiest ones are
<i>actual</i> mushrooms and <i>actual</i> bamboo shoots.

00:12:17.624 --> 00:12:20.144
And not the chocolate snacks, you know,

00:12:20.169 --> 00:12:23.484
The <i>Kinoko no Yama</i> and <i>Takenoko no Sato</i>.

00:12:24.577 --> 00:12:28.850
- She though <i>actual</i> ones.
- So I don't want you to misunderstand that

00:12:29.597 --> 00:12:32.235
Our decision when it comes
to the chocolate snacks.

00:12:32.937 --> 00:12:36.537
When it comes to the
actual vegetables, you know?

00:12:37.754 --> 00:12:39.376
All mushrooms are good!

00:12:39.493 --> 00:12:42.157
- We're not like Nerissa or Biboo.
- No!

00:12:42.182 --> 00:12:44.662
- All mushrooms are delicious.
- Mushrooms are very very yummy.

00:12:44.687 --> 00:12:46.012
But what about Nameko?

00:12:46.687 --> 00:12:48.116
Nameko!

00:12:48.338 --> 00:12:51.510
- It might be a bit tricky.
- Maybe it's still a bit tricky.

00:12:51.590 --> 00:12:55.213
I like it, but it's a bit
difficult to eat a lot of them.

00:12:55.273 --> 00:12:59.406
But to set the score right, when it comes
to the chocolate snack, we like...

00:13:03.556 --> 00:13:04.690
Neither!

00:13:07.241 --> 00:13:08.741
Yeah, you know it's chocolate.

00:13:08.881 --> 00:13:10.362
The actual veggie is yummy.

00:13:10.862 --> 00:13:12.922
I prefer to have the actual vegetables.

00:13:13.262 --> 00:13:14.682
No chocolate. No snacks.

00:13:15.840 --> 00:13:16.840
Got it?

00:13:17.194 --> 00:13:19.184
- Understood?
- Understood.

00:13:19.624 --> 00:13:24.066
That is the end of the
Takenoko vs Kinoko debate.

00:13:24.226 --> 00:13:25.326
The misunderstanding.

00:13:26.626 --> 00:13:28.047
It's all cleared.

00:13:28.647 --> 00:13:31.408
We can start our day
knowing that it's all good now.

00:13:33.399 --> 00:13:40.645
Well, today we wanted to introduce
our first thoughts about Advent.

00:13:40.805 --> 00:13:42.466
What was it like meeting Advent?

00:13:44.388 --> 00:13:46.730
Moco-chan prepared
something very special.

00:13:47.848 --> 00:13:48.848
I hope you like it.

00:13:49.632 --> 00:13:50.813
I did my best, okay?

00:13:51.854 --> 00:13:54.776
First up, we have Shiori!

00:13:57.728 --> 00:14:00.610
Our first thoughts of Shiori.

00:14:00.630 --> 00:14:02.911
The first thing she said, I
remember it very clearly.

00:14:02.931 --> 00:14:04.212
She went, Shiori!

00:14:04.632 --> 00:14:06.933
It was really cute.

00:14:07.113 --> 00:14:10.675
So cute that I kind of
thought like, is she joking?

00:14:12.476 --> 00:14:13.917
It was that big of a gap!

00:14:14.637 --> 00:14:16.138
- It's very good.
- Oh, right?

00:14:16.238 --> 00:14:21.293
And then she was like really, really
stoic and kind of like a bit of a

00:14:21.426 --> 00:14:27.343
hard to read ear to her, so it was a very
interesting first impression, I think.

00:14:27.583 --> 00:14:28.924
Very like <i>kakkoike</i>.

00:14:29.268 --> 00:14:30.303
Yeah.

00:14:30.665 --> 00:14:34.215
I think to be completely honest,
we were a bit scared of her at first,

00:14:34.240 --> 00:14:38.868
you know, especially with her
really strong piercing bird-like eyes.

00:14:40.189 --> 00:14:41.650
But I feel like, you know,

00:14:43.151 --> 00:14:46.113
It was a bit of a funny
feeling at first, you know?

00:14:47.969 --> 00:14:50.695
We felt a bit troubled actually
because we wanted to get

00:14:50.720 --> 00:14:54.539
to know Shiori better, but
we just felt like we couldn't.

00:14:54.759 --> 00:14:58.361
Like, really like, we're like, uh, FUWAMOCO
what are we doing wrong, you know?

00:14:59.722 --> 00:15:02.451
We would kind of think
of strategies, you know.

00:15:02.476 --> 00:15:05.303
Things to get her
to maybe warm up to us.

00:15:05.543 --> 00:15:07.436
- Or us to warm up to her.
- Right?

00:15:08.309 --> 00:15:09.309
You know?

00:15:09.496 --> 00:15:13.745
She was a really tough book to crack,
but all of a sudden, that just changed.

00:15:14.325 --> 00:15:16.366
And we don't feel that
way anymore, you know?

00:15:16.406 --> 00:15:17.806
Shiori's really, really sweet.

00:15:18.546 --> 00:15:22.587
I think she definitely tries to put
on a strong face, like, I'm so cool.

00:15:22.927 --> 00:15:24.607
But she's actually really, really sweet.

00:15:24.907 --> 00:15:27.648
And even I feel like a
bit shy sometimes, too.

00:15:29.088 --> 00:15:30.909
- She's really dependable.
- Dependable!

00:15:30.929 --> 00:15:34.829
And she has so, so, so
much knowledge in that.

00:15:35.029 --> 00:15:36.730
We wish we could
Google search her brain.

00:15:36.940 --> 00:15:39.070
Right? She has a lot
going on in her noggin.

00:15:40.150 --> 00:15:44.291
So, it'd be nice to search
it, but... You can't do that.

00:15:44.311 --> 00:15:46.681
Yeah, we don't really want
to overburden her with

00:15:46.706 --> 00:15:50.192
All our FUWAMOCO questions
and requests and stuff like that.

00:15:50.261 --> 00:15:54.585
Yeah. And that's the other thing,
you know, if the other Advent members,

00:15:54.610 --> 00:15:58.094
If they let us be needy,
right, we're gonna be needy.

00:15:59.035 --> 00:16:01.296
It's not good. They need to not spoil us.

00:16:01.817 --> 00:16:03.678
We love Shiori!

00:16:03.778 --> 00:16:07.501
We love you Shiori!

00:16:07.521 --> 00:16:09.783
We hope you like
Moco-chan's illustration.

00:16:10.003 --> 00:16:12.905
I did my best. I really captured your eyes.

00:16:13.386 --> 00:16:14.586
I think so, I think so.

00:16:14.827 --> 00:16:15.947
Ruffians, what do you think?

00:16:17.202 --> 00:16:18.730
Does it look just like her?

00:16:19.249 --> 00:16:20.249
It does, right?

00:16:20.674 --> 00:16:21.729
"Adorable?"

00:16:22.693 --> 00:16:24.993
"It's cute?" Thank you! Thank you!

00:16:25.749 --> 00:16:26.960
OK, well...

00:16:27.404 --> 00:16:31.325
Next Advent member is Biboo!

00:16:32.165 --> 00:16:36.706
I think one of the first things
she said was "I'm really shy."

00:16:37.267 --> 00:16:39.787
But that lasted really
for about 30 minutes.

00:16:39.887 --> 00:16:43.989
I don't think she's that shy.

00:16:44.509 --> 00:16:46.569
Maybe she's shy like us.

00:16:46.870 --> 00:16:47.870
Maybe.

00:16:48.547 --> 00:16:50.187
Do you think we're shy?
I think we're shy.

00:16:50.873 --> 00:16:52.433
Maybe we're the same kind of shy.

00:16:52.733 --> 00:16:56.336
But she's very cute and a
very sharp rock, you know?

00:16:57.176 --> 00:16:59.309
I think she kind of
downplays her powers.

00:16:59.402 --> 00:17:00.402
Yeah.

00:17:00.557 --> 00:17:02.197
You know, that makes her a bit cuter too.

00:17:03.221 --> 00:17:04.342
But we can see through that.

00:17:04.822 --> 00:17:07.384
And I think she's really
a master of her craft.

00:17:07.564 --> 00:17:09.826
Yeah. I mean, she's had
years and years and years

00:17:10.166 --> 00:17:12.532
- Right?
- To become a beautiful gem, so,

00:17:12.987 --> 00:17:14.310
Very very sharp.

00:17:15.753 --> 00:17:17.794
At first we were really
surprised to hear that

00:17:17.819 --> 00:17:21.830
She likes to play games for a long
time and that's normal for her, but

00:17:22.084 --> 00:17:24.078
We were also really happy
because we know that

00:17:24.246 --> 00:17:27.665
FUWAMOCO, we're not
quite like that, too, so y'know

00:17:27.690 --> 00:17:29.144
Sometimes it can be a bit tough.

00:17:29.671 --> 00:17:33.190
It's good to have lots of different
flavors within Advent, you know?

00:17:33.215 --> 00:17:35.895
I'm just happy that she likes it
and that she's not pushing herself.

00:17:37.260 --> 00:17:38.854
She's definitely the gamer.

00:17:40.273 --> 00:17:42.457
I think there was one time where

00:17:42.583 --> 00:17:45.763
there was a reference that she wasn't
a gamer, and Biboo got

00:17:46.063 --> 00:17:47.691
- Kinda grumpy.
- It's like "excuse me?!"

00:17:47.716 --> 00:17:48.716
Right. Right?

00:17:50.371 --> 00:17:54.780
She's super sweet and super
cute and. you know, she just

00:17:55.270 --> 00:17:57.179
We get this really,
really strong feeling that

00:17:57.204 --> 00:18:00.250
We <i>really</i> need to protect her extra hard.

00:18:01.010 --> 00:18:03.410
Even though she's always
smiling, she's strong.

00:18:03.590 --> 00:18:05.171
She's probably fine.

00:18:05.231 --> 00:18:10.154
We worry about her, so we want
to make sure she's smiling too.

00:18:10.815 --> 00:18:12.576
We feel very protectable.

00:18:12.636 --> 00:18:15.498
We're protecting her smile too, sorry.

00:18:17.759 --> 00:18:21.461
I was thinking though, you know...
Biboo has her little flaps, right?

00:18:21.661 --> 00:18:25.963
They look kind of like ears, but...
And like, Biboo can fly too, right?

00:18:26.083 --> 00:18:29.373
So I was thinking that... I don't
know if Biboo can do this, but

00:18:29.398 --> 00:18:32.146
It'd be nice to kind of fly
together with Biboo's flaps.

00:18:32.546 --> 00:18:37.869
And then like, our twin
tails could go like... Yeah.

00:18:38.069 --> 00:18:40.090
We can fly as a group together.

00:18:40.110 --> 00:18:42.051
I guess with Nerissa too.

00:18:42.651 --> 00:18:44.612
Shiori can just ride on the back.

00:18:44.637 --> 00:18:46.479
Oh really? I was gonna
say we'll make her walk.

00:18:49.125 --> 00:18:55.673
And then Biboo's song cover, it
actually makes us really, really emotional.

00:18:56.795 --> 00:18:58.038
